node.text: When we take care of people, we take care of the planet. We’re donating 100M disease-resistant coffee trees by 2025 to help farmers and their communities, and committing to reduce our landfill waste by 50% by 2030.

node.title: Caring for Our Planet & Our People

node.text: Why is Nitro Cold Brew so whoa? Bill Nye explains.

node.title: Bill Nye Presents Nitro Cold Brew

node.accessibility_caption: Gigi stands wearing a Starbucks green apron and smiling at the camera.

node.text:
For Gigi, getting a bachelor’s degree felt like a dream that would never come true. “For a long time … I thought I was just never going to graduate college and (was going to) be a disappointment to my parents.”

Plot twist: Gigi is about to begin her senior year of college working towards her bachelor's degree in film and media through the Starbucks College Achievement Plan (SCAP). Through the program, our eligible partners (employees) attend @ASUOnline with 100% tuition coverage. The program connects Starbucks partners with more than 100 bachelor's degree programs, all offered fully online.

Gigi’s focus on film and media stems from her passion for storytelling and performing. She recently recorded a solo songwriting project, found a concert and tours management internship, hosted a community open mic event at her Starbucks store and auditioned for – and earned – the spot in a Starbucks 50th anniversary television commercial spotlighting the SCAP program.

“When I started working at Starbucks, I had no idea – no idea – that it would open so many doors for me,” says Gigi.

node.text: Caramel forever. 😋 Caramel Ribbon Crunch Frappuccino® Drink

node.accessibility_caption: Two women wearing Starbucks green aprons. One holds a protein box and the other an orange FoodShare crate.

node.text:
100% of our U.S. company-owned stores are now donating food to local food banks. This program—called FoodShare—has helped provide nearly 34 million ready-to-eat meals in partnership with organizations like @feedingamerica.

And our work doesn’t stop there. We will continue to help our communities fight hunger because we believe that everyone should have access to nourishing food.

To learn more about the FoodShare program, check out our Instagram Story.

node.accessibility_caption: A hand holds a bag of Starbucks Reserve whole bean coffee with blossoms and bright morning sun  in the background.

node.text: Make your morning bright. Enjoy notes of orange blossom, milk chocolate, and a sweet caramel finish. Find @starbucksreserve Bolivia Sol de la Mañana at select US Starbucks stores.
